title: Lewica Party Affairs

@campaigning
title: Campaigning
new-page: true
is-card: true
card-image: img/party_cards/campaigning.png
tags: lewica_party_affairs
frequency: 100
max-visits: 36
on-arrival: month_actions += 1

= Campaigning

Whether or not there is a formal campaign, the SLD is always trying to broaden its voter base. Who should receive the month's attention?

- @campaign_urban_professionals: Urban professionals.
- @campaign_urban_working_class: Urban working-class voters.
- @campaign_unaffiliated_youth: Young secular and unaffiliated voters.
- @campaign_women_under_50: Women under 50.
- @campaign_rural_west: Rural and small-town western Poland.
- @campaign_catholic_nonpracticing: Catholic but non-practicing voters.
- @post_event: We either do not want to or cannot campaign right now.

@campaign_urban_professionals
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.urban_professionals_left += 2.6 * eff;
Q.unaffiliated_left += 0.8 * eff;
Q.media_reach = Math.min(10, Q.media_reach + 0.4);
Q.left_brand_strength = Math.min(10, Q.left_brand_strength + 0.2);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.2);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.2);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.25 * eff;
Q.left_campaigns_urban_professionals += 1;
!}

The campaign buys targeted media and event work in Warsaw, Krakow, Wroclaw, Poznan, and Gdansk. This helps voters who are culturally liberal but instinctively prefer PO.

- @post_event: Continue.

@campaign_urban_working_class
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.urban_working_class_left += 3.0 * eff;
Q.age_50_65_left += 0.8 * eff;
Q.age_65_plus_left += 0.4 * eff;
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.pps_up_dissent - 0.4);
Q.sld_apparatus_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_strength + 0.1);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.3 * eff;
Q.left_campaigns_urban_working_class += 1;
!}

The message leans into wages, pensions, post-industrial cities, and the memory of a left that once spoke to workers rather than only to television studios.

- @post_event: Continue.

@campaign_unaffiliated_youth
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.under_30_left += 3.1 * eff;
Q.unaffiliated_left += 2.0 * eff;
Q.lgbtq_left += 1.0 * eff;
Q.media_reach = Math.min(10, Q.media_reach + 0.5);
Q.secularization_tide = Math.min(10, Q.secularization_tide + 0.2);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.3);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.4);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.35 * eff;
Q.left_campaigns_unaffiliated_youth += 1;
!}

The party tests a sharper secular and generational message. It is the right language for younger non-practicing voters, but the apparatus worries about looking unserious.

- @post_event: Continue.

@campaign_women_under_50
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.women_under_50_left += 2.8 * eff;
Q.under_30_left += 0.8 * eff;
Q.unaffiliated_left += 0.8 * eff;
Q.civil_society_capital = Math.min(10, Q.civil_society_capital + 0.2);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.2);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.pps_up_dissent - 0.2);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.3 * eff;
!}

The party talks about labor-market discrimination, childcare, reproductive autonomy, and the everyday costs of a conservative state.

- @post_event: Continue.

@campaign_rural_west
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.rural_west_left += 2.4 * eff;
Q.urban_working_class_left += 0.5 * eff;
Q.psl_relation = Math.max(-10, Q.psl_relation - 1);
Q.sld_apparatus_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_strength + 0.2);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.2 * eff;
!}

The SLD works county-level networks in western Poland, where post-state-farm memory and local government still give the left a faint opening.

- @post_event: Continue.

@campaign_catholic_nonpracticing
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
const eff = 1 - Q.dissent;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.catholic_nonpracticing_left += 2.5 * eff;
Q.women_over_50_left += 0.6 * eff;
Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment = Math.max(0, Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment - 0.2);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.2);
Q.left_campaign_bonus += 0.25 * eff;
!}

The party separates private Catholic identity from clerical political power, trying to reach voters who no longer obey the pulpit but do not think of themselves as anti-religious.

- @post_event: Continue.

@fundraising
title: Fundraising
new-page: true
is-card: true
card-image: img/party_cards/fundraising.png
tags: lewica_party_affairs
view-if: fundraising_timer <= 0
on-arrival: fundraising_timer = 12

= Fundraising

The party cannot exist without money. It receives yearly dues, but the level of dues changes both resources and internal discipline.

- @fundraising_maintain: Maintain our current dues.
- @fundraising_reduce: Reduce dues.
- @fundraising_increase: Increase dues.

@fundraising_maintain
subtitle: We gain [+ dues +] resources per year.

We maintain our current dues.

- @post_event: Continue.

@fundraising_reduce
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues - 1 +] resources per year. -1 resource.
choose-if: dues > 1 and resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We lack resources, or dues are already at their floor.
on-arrival: {!
Q.dues -= 1;
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent - 0.8);
Q.sld_modernizers_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_modernizers_dissent - 0.8);
Q.tr_residue_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.tr_residue_dissent - 0.8);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.pps_up_dissent - 0.8);
if (Q.dissent_percent < 5) Q.resources += 1;
if (Q.dissent_percent > 30) Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.month_actions += 1;
!}

Members appreciate the relief, especially in weaker local branches, but the annual income stream shrinks.

- @post_event: Continue.

@fundraising_increase
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues + 1 +] resources per year. +1 resource.
view-if: dues <= 4
on-arrival: {!
Q.dues += 1;
Q.resources += 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.urban_working_class_left -= 0.8;
Q.age_65_plus_left -= 0.4;
if (Q.unemployment >= 10) {
    Q.urban_working_class_left -= 1.2;
    Q.under_30_left -= 0.6;
}
if (Q.dues >= 5) {
    Q.urban_working_class_left -= Q.dues * 0.3;
    Q.under_30_left -= Q.dues * 0.2;
}
Q.month_actions += 1;
!}

The apparatus gains money now and income later, but members with thinner wallets feel the extra burden.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology
title: Questions of Ideology
new-page: true
is-card: true
card-image: img/party_cards/ideology.png
tags: lewica_party_affairs
view-if: ideology_timer <= 0
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; old_ideology = ideology; ideology_timer = 18
max-visits: 3

= Questions of Ideology

The SLD is torn between survival, programmatic left politics, and cultural modernization. What should guide the party for now?

[? if ideology != 0: We previously chose a [+ ideology +] line. Changing it will unsettle factions. ?]

- @ideology_apparatus: Institutional social democracy and coalition survival.
- @ideology_labor: Labor, wages, pensions, and union-linked economics.
- @ideology_modernizing: Modernizing urban progressivism.
- @ideology_anticlerical: Explicit secular and anti-clerical politics.
- @ideology_left_unity: Broad left unity, even at the cost of SLD control.

@ideology_apparatus
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "institutional") Q.ideology_changed = 1;
Q.ideology = "institutional";
Q.sld_apparatus_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_strength + 0.8);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent - 0.8);
Q.sld_modernizers_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_dissent + 0.4);
Q.ko_relation += 2;
Q.psl_relation += 1;
!}
go-to: ideology_changed if ideology_changed = 1

The party chooses discipline, parliamentary seriousness, and coalition viability over ideological sharpness.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology_labor
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "labor") Q.ideology_changed = 1;
Q.ideology = "labor";
Q.pps_up_strength = Math.min(10, Q.pps_up_strength + 0.8);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.pps_up_dissent - 0.5);
Q.urban_working_class_left += 1.0 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.3);
Q.razem_relation += 2;
!}
go-to: ideology_changed if ideology_changed = 1

The party talks less about nostalgia and more about wages, contracts, public services, and insecure work.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology_modernizing
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "modernizing") Q.ideology_changed = 1;
Q.ideology = "modernizing";
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.8);
Q.sld_modernizers_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_modernizers_dissent - 0.6);
Q.urban_professionals_left += 1.0 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.under_30_left += 0.8 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.4);
Q.ko_relation += 1;
!}
go-to: ideology_changed if ideology_changed = 1

The SLD tries to look less like a post-communist inheritance machine and more like a contemporary European left party.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology_anticlerical
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "secular") Q.ideology_changed = 1;
Q.ideology = "secular";
Q.secularization_tide = Math.min(10, Q.secularization_tide + 0.4);
Q.unaffiliated_left += 1.0 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.lgbtq_left += 0.8 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.4);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.5);
Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment = Math.max(0, Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment - 0.5);
!}
go-to: ideology_changed if ideology_changed = 1

The party puts church-state separation at the center of its identity. It clarifies the brand, but narrows some coalition paths.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology_left_unity
on-arrival: {!
if (Q.ideology && Q.ideology != "left unity") Q.ideology_changed = 1;
Q.ideology = "left unity";
Q.tr_residue_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.tr_residue_dissent - 0.5);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.pps_up_dissent - 0.4);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.5);
Q.civil_society_capital = Math.min(10, Q.civil_society_capital + 0.4);
Q.razem_relation += 2;
Q.left_brand_strength = Math.min(10, Q.left_brand_strength + 0.2);
!}
go-to: ideology_changed if ideology_changed = 1

The party prepares itself to bargain with non-SLD left actors. This is promising, but it weakens apparatus control.

- @post_event: Continue.

@ideology_changed
on-arrival: {!
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.5);
Q.sld_modernizers_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_dissent + 0.5);
Q.tr_residue_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.tr_residue_dissent + 0.5);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.pps_up_dissent + 0.5);
Q.ideology_changed = 0;
!}

Changing ideological direction makes many in the party feel unmoored.

- @post_event: Continue.

@opponents
title: Choosing Our Opponents
new-page: true
is-card: true
card-image: img/party_cards/opponents.png
tags: lewica_party_affairs
view-if: year <= 2015 and opponents_timer <= 0
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; opponents_timer = 18
max-visits: 3

= Choosing Our Opponents

In media and campaign material, who should be treated as the primary opponent?

[? if opponents != 0: Previously, we aimed primarily at [+ opponents +]. ?]

- @opponent_pis: PiS and the conservative state project.
- @opponent_ko: PO and the liberal establishment.
- @opponent_church: Clerical political power.
- @opponent_farright: Far-right nationalism.
- @opponent_all: The entire anti-left political order.

@opponent_pis
on-arrival: {!
Q.opponents = "PiS";
Q.sld_apparatus_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_strength + 0.4);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.3);
Q.ko_relation += 2;
Q.pis_relation -= 3;
Q.pis_kaczynski_strength = Math.min(10, Q.pis_kaczynski_strength + 0.2);
Q.catholic_nonpracticing_pis -= 0.8;
Q.urban_working_class_pis -= 0.6;
!}

The message is legible to anti-PiS voters and coalition-minded elites, but it risks making the SLD look like PO's smaller assistant.

- @post_event: Continue.

@opponent_ko
on-arrival: {!
Q.opponents = "PO liberal establishment";
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.4);
Q.pps_up_strength = Math.min(10, Q.pps_up_strength + 0.4);
Q.tr_residue_strength = Math.min(10, Q.tr_residue_strength + 0.3);
Q.ko_relation -= 4;
Q.razem_relation += 2;
Q.urban_professionals_ko -= 0.5;
Q.urban_working_class_ko -= 0.8;
Q.urban_working_class_left += 0.7 * (1 - Q.dissent);
!}

The party attacks privatization, broken public services, and complacent liberalism. It distinguishes the left, but damages coalition trust.

- @post_event: Continue.

@opponent_church
on-arrival: {!
Q.opponents = "clerical political power";
Q.secularization_tide = Math.min(10, Q.secularization_tide + 0.3);
Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment = Math.max(0, Q.vatican_episcopate_alignment - 0.5);
Q.unaffiliated_left += 1.0 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.lgbtq_left += 0.8 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.catholic_practicing_left -= 0.4;
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.4);
!}

The SLD revives one of its clearest issues: a secular state. It mobilizes secular voters while hardening religious opposition.

- @post_event: Continue.

@opponent_farright
on-arrival: {!
Q.opponents = "far-right nationalism";
Q.mw_onr_mobilization = Math.max(0, Q.mw_onr_mobilization - 0.3);
Q.konf_poll = Math.max(0, Q.konf_poll - 0.2);
Q.konf_mentzen_strength = Math.max(0, Q.konf_mentzen_strength - 0.1);
Q.civil_society_capital = Math.min(10, Q.civil_society_capital + 0.2);
Q.sld_modernizers_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_modernizers_dissent - 0.2);
Q.under_30_konf -= 0.5;
!}

The party treats organized nationalism as a public threat rather than as eccentric youth politics.

- @post_event: Continue.

@opponent_all
on-arrival: {!
Q.opponents = "the entire anti-left order";
Q.pps_up_strength = Math.min(10, Q.pps_up_strength + 0.5);
Q.tr_residue_strength = Math.min(10, Q.tr_residue_strength + 0.3);
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent + 0.7);
Q.ko_relation -= 2;
Q.psl_relation -= 2;
Q.razem_relation += 1;
Q.left_brand_strength = Math.min(10, Q.left_brand_strength + 0.2);
!}

The rhetoric is sharp, but it can make every future negotiation harder.

- @post_event: Continue.

@inter_party_relationships
title: Inter-Party Relationships
