= International Relations

Through European socialist networks and foreign-policy contacts, SLD can borrow credibility and ideas from abroad.

- @international_snd: Build ties with S&D and European social democrats.
- @international_germany: Work the German and Brussels channels.
- @international_ukraine: Develop a clearer Ukraine and eastern policy.
- @international_atlantic: Maintain NATO and US-security credibility.
- @international_none: We do not need international contacts now.

@international_snd
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.eu_institutional_alignment = Math.min(10, Q.eu_institutional_alignment + 0.4);
Q.sld_modernizers_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_modernizers_strength + 0.3);
Q.left_brand_strength = Math.min(10, Q.left_brand_strength + 0.2);
!}

European social democrats give the party some vocabulary for renewal beyond post-communist defensiveness.

- @post_event: Continue.

@international_germany
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.german_bilateral = Math.min(10, Q.german_bilateral + 0.3);
Q.eu_institutional_alignment = Math.min(10, Q.eu_institutional_alignment + 0.2);
Q.ko_relation += 1;
Q.sld_apparatus_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.sld_apparatus_dissent - 0.1);
!}

The SLD leans on predictable European channels: useful for seriousness, not useful for insurgent energy.

- @post_event: Continue.

@international_ukraine
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.ukrainian_alignment = Math.min(10, Q.ukrainian_alignment + 0.4);
Q.russian_threat_level = Math.max(Q.russian_threat_level, 5);
Q.belarusian_eastern_minority_left += 1.0 * (1 - Q.dissent);
Q.pps_up_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.pps_up_dissent + 0.2);
!}

After Maidan and Crimea, eastern policy is no longer a specialist issue. The party starts catching up.

- @post_event: Continue.

@international_atlantic
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 1;
Q.party_resources = Q.resources;
Q.us_alignment = Math.min(10, Q.us_alignment + 0.3);
Q.ko_relation += 1;
Q.sld_apparatus_strength = Math.min(10, Q.sld_apparatus_strength + 0.2);
Q.tr_residue_dissent = Math.min(10, Q.tr_residue_dissent + 0.2);
!}

The SLD keeps the old NATO-accession-era line: pro-Western, predictable, and security-minded.

- @post_event: Continue.

@international_none

The party stays focused on domestic survival.

- @post_event: Continue.

